<section id="command-ascii">
<title>ASCII</title>
<indexterm><primary>ASCII</primary></indexterm>

<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term>Synopsis</term>
<listitem>
<synopsis><command>ASCII</command> <parameter>character</parameter></synopsis>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Description</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Outputs the number from 0-255 that represents <parameter>character</parameter> in your current code page.
</para>

<para>
ASCII interprets control characters as representing backslashed punctuation and outputs the character code corresponding to the punctuation character without the backslash.
</para>

<para>
This command is called "ASCII" because &PRODUCTNAME; was originally restricted to the ASCII character set.
</para>

</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Example</term>
<listitem>
<programlisting><userinput>SHOW ASCII "a</userinput>
97</programlisting>

<programlisting><userinput>SHOW ASCII "A</userinput>
65</programlisting>

<programlisting><userinput>SHOW ASCII "|(|</userinput>
40</programlisting>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>See Also</term>
<listitem><simplelist>
<member><link linkend="command-rawascii">RAWASCII</link></member>
<member><link linkend="command-char">CHAR</link></member>
</simplelist></listitem>
</varlistentry>

</variablelist>
</section>
